Ad Text:
12 + 12 + 12-month contract - July Start
Baseline Security Clearance required
Canberra, ACT - Some WFH available
EL1 equivalent | Azure / M365 / Dynamics365 and DevOps platforms. 

Our client, a Federal Government agency focused on developing policies and programs that support Australian industry, science, resources, energy, emissions reduction, and small and family businesses, is seeking an experienced Cloud Solutions Architect.

Duties of the Cloud Solutions Architect.

Provide senior-level expertise as a Cloud Engineer or Solution Architect;
Design, develop, and maintain Azure DevOps pipelines to support efficient CI/CD processes and deployment automation;
Configure and manage Azure Virtual Networks, including hybrid network architectures and cloud-native web ingress patterns;
Ensure cloud solutions align with cyber security frameworks and controls, including ISM, OWASP principles, and Essential Eight requirements;
Apply in-depth technical knowledge of the Microsoft Azure cloud platform to design and implement robust cloud architectures;
Translate business requirements into detailed technical designs, supported by clear documentation, diagrams, and precise technical specifications.

Skills and Experience Required

Demonstrated experience in understanding business requirements and solutioning designs for Azure based cloud environments into HLD and DLD as well as reusable architecture patterns;
Demonstrated experience applying information security concepts and best practices including Information Security Manual (ISM);
Experience with a broad range of cloud technologies including Azure AI, ML and Cognitive services, Data Solutions, DevOps, CI/CD, Integration solutions, and API/Services Oriented Architecture;
Ability to work with limited guidance in an Agile environment.

How to Apply
For a copy of the full job description, including the application instructions please get in touch with Jess P at the Recruitment Hive by clicking the Quick Apply button. Alternatively, you can reach Jess P on (02) 6299 1006 to discuss further.

Please note, applications close on Friday, 24 April 2026 at midday, Canberra time.

